WEBVTT

00:00.195 --> 00:03.648
- Stand back.
- [X-RAY WHIRS, CLICKS]

00:05.814 --> 00:08.650
- What was his temp?
- 102.

00:15.226 --> 00:17.708
Yeah, he's junky and wheezy
on both sides.

00:17.742 --> 00:19.710
Zach's been coughing,
uh, gasping.

00:19.735 --> 00:21.180
It's terrible.

00:21.711 --> 00:23.440
Bibasilar infiltrates.

00:23.465 --> 00:26.800
- What does that mean?
- Well, most likely, pneumonia.

00:27.018 --> 00:30.454
April, let's start vancomycin,
40 milligrams per kilogram,

00:30.488 --> 00:32.177
and we'll get him admitted to the PICU.

00:32.202 --> 00:33.522
- Oh, God.
- Don't worry.

00:33.547 --> 00:35.114
We've got great pediatricians.

00:35.139 --> 00:37.254
Yeah, you can go up with him.

00:41.297 --> 00:42.897
Dr. Charles,
why didn't you tell me

00:42.922 --> 00:44.919
the truth about my father?

00:45.512 --> 00:47.380
And... and what is that?

00:47.405 --> 00:49.948
That he is a psychopath.

00:51.008 --> 00:52.909
I looked at his chart.

00:52.944 --> 00:55.480
- You did, did ya?
- Yes.

00:55.717 --> 00:57.671
Before you looked at
your father's chart,

00:57.882 --> 00:59.672
did you agree to cosign his loan?

00:59.697 --> 01:01.125
- No.
- You didn't?

01:01.189 --> 01:02.823
Could that maybe be because

01:02.848 --> 01:05.450
somewhere, you already
knew what he was?

01:05.476 --> 01:07.194
You could have told me.

01:07.219 --> 01:09.847
Sarah, I couldn't tell you.
You know I couldn't.

01:09.872 --> 01:11.000
Yeah, because he locked you up

01:11.025 --> 01:12.792
with doctor-patient confidentiality.

01:12.817 --> 01:14.483
He made it so you couldn't interfere,

01:14.508 --> 01:16.740
went to you with a bogus complaint.

01:17.135 --> 01:19.503
God, the premeditation,
the manipulation,

01:19.537 --> 01:22.064
it's... he is disgusting.

01:22.089 --> 01:23.234
Or he's just somebody

01:23.259 --> 01:25.538
who is incapable of
empathetic feelings.

01:25.815 --> 01:28.016
Sarah, look, I'm so sorry,

01:28.041 --> 01:31.147
I can't imagine how
difficult this must be,

01:31.751 --> 01:34.129
but I would just hope that... that...

01:34.894 --> 01:37.262
there might be something
positive in your knowing.

01:37.287 --> 01:39.745
- Positive?
- Well, just the clarity.

01:39.934 --> 01:42.798
The clarity of the revelation
that your father was who he was

01:42.823 --> 01:44.706
and he was born that way,

01:44.731 --> 01:45.897
and that his leaving

01:45.922 --> 01:48.413
had absolutely nothing to do with you.

01:48.438 --> 01:50.213
That's my consolation?

01:51.714 --> 01:55.092
Dr. Charles, after all
of these years...

01:55.364 --> 01:56.664
all these years,

01:56.689 --> 01:58.584
my father finally walks
back into my life,

01:58.609 --> 01:59.933
and it turns out...

02:02.043 --> 02:03.841
he never loved me.

02:04.819 --> 02:08.396
He can never love me.

02:08.422 --> 02:11.390
<i>[SOFT, SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

02:11.922 --> 02:17.539
<i>♪ </i>

02:18.851 --> 02:20.285
[PHONE RINGS]

02:20.310 --> 02:21.681
ED?

02:22.653 --> 02:23.820
Yeah.

02:23.845 --> 02:26.605
Dr. Halstead, it's the PICU.

02:26.940 --> 02:29.065
This is Dr. Halstead.

02:29.319 --> 02:32.092
Yeah, that's right. Zach
Womack, four months old.

02:33.753 --> 02:35.290
Really?

02:38.195 --> 02:40.610
Hey, thank you.

02:40.671 --> 02:43.346
That baby we just sent
up to the PICU...

02:43.987 --> 02:45.655
he never made it there.

02:45.774 --> 02:48.107
<i>[OMINOUS MUSIC]</i>

02:48.132 --> 02:54.718
- Synced and corrected by martythecrazy -
- www.addic7ed.com -

02:55.458 --> 02:57.292
- We got off the elevator,
a nurse met us,

02:57.317 --> 02:59.438
and she said that Zach
needed some sort of test.

02:59.463 --> 03:01.449
A scan.
She said he needed a scan.

03:01.474 --> 03:03.010
She took him away
and she never brought him back.

03:03.035 --> 03:04.962
Did you follow up
with Radiology?

03:04.987 --> 03:06.056
No scans were ordered.

03:06.081 --> 03:07.461
And the nurse they've described

03:07.486 --> 03:09.715
doesn't match anyone on my staff.

03:10.026 --> 03:11.927
Has someone kidnapped our baby?

03:11.952 --> 03:13.939
We can't be sure about that yet.

03:13.964 --> 03:16.009
Oh, no.

03:16.810 --> 03:18.237
No.

03:18.544 --> 03:20.006
Call a Code Pink.

03:20.031 --> 03:22.088
Tell Security to put the
hospital on lockdown.

03:22.113 --> 03:25.086
The ED, including
Trauma, goes on bypass.

03:25.111 --> 03:28.912
Until further notice,
no one comes in or out.

03:29.292 --> 03:32.090
I promise you we're going
to find your baby.

03:32.115 --> 03:35.083
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

03:35.372 --> 03:38.546
<i>♪ </i>

03:38.867 --> 03:40.920
Earl, the hospital's
going on lockdown.

03:40.945 --> 03:42.478
- Get to your post.
- Yes, sir.

03:42.513 --> 03:44.681
This is Cole.
Code Pink. Code Pink.

03:44.715 --> 03:46.316
<i>Copy that, Code Pink.</i>

03:46.455 --> 03:48.856
<i>♪ </i>

03:48.986 --> 03:51.937
Get that patient in now.
Hospital's going on lockdown.

03:51.962 --> 03:53.448
[DOOR BEEPS]

03:53.473 --> 03:54.692
You're going to Treatment Two.

03:54.717 --> 03:56.255
Jill Fisher, 25 years old.

03:56.280 --> 03:58.148
Her VW Bug got T-boned by a pickup.

03:58.173 --> 03:59.928
Seat belt sign and
chest wall abrasions.

03:59.953 --> 04:01.422
- Gonna need X-ray.
- Help me!

04:01.447 --> 04:03.000
- I'm her mother.
- We are, sweetheart.

04:03.025 --> 04:04.996
- [SCREAMS]
- BP, 100 over 70.

04:05.021 --> 04:08.113
Heart rate, 96. She's satting at 88%.

04:08.138 --> 04:10.640
- Is she gonna be okay?
- We haven't examined her yet,

04:10.674 --> 04:12.431
but we're gonna take good care of her.

04:12.456 --> 04:13.423
All right,
let's get her transferred

04:13.448 --> 04:14.762
and onto the monitors.

04:14.787 --> 04:16.975
One, two, and three.

04:17.387 --> 04:20.199
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

04:20.591 --> 04:22.630
- Doris, 50 of fentanyl.
- On it.

04:22.655 --> 04:24.340
- Is she gonna be okay?
- Ma'am, please come with me.

04:24.365 --> 04:26.275
- I... I love you, honey.
- Careful.

04:26.300 --> 04:29.164
[COUGHING, WHEEZING]

04:29.352 --> 04:31.393
<i>♪ </i>

04:31.523 --> 04:33.451
[X-RAY WHIRS, CLICKS]

04:33.693 --> 04:35.873
<i>♪ </i>

04:35.934 --> 04:37.752
Multiple right
posterior rib fractures

04:37.777 --> 04:39.123
and a pneumothorax.

04:39.148 --> 04:41.154
She needs a chest tube.
20 of lidocaine.

04:41.179 --> 04:43.884
- [DISTRESSED BREATHING]
- Sats are 82 and falling.

04:43.909 --> 04:45.309
All right, so hustle.

04:45.453 --> 04:52.692
<i>♪ </i>

04:54.315 --> 04:56.038
Ready for the tube.

04:56.313 --> 04:58.426
[SCREAMS, SOBBING]

04:58.451 --> 05:01.143
She's at 90.
Sats are coming up.

05:01.168 --> 05:03.731
Uh, we're gonna need
a repeat chest X-ray,

05:03.756 --> 05:06.988
and let's order a CT
c-spine, abdomen and pelvis.

05:07.013 --> 05:08.997
<i>Code Pink. Code Pink.</i>

05:09.022 --> 05:11.624
- Missing kid?
- Yeah.

05:11.649 --> 05:14.567
Probably the baby Dr.
Halstead sent to PICU.

05:14.592 --> 05:16.955
[SIRENS BLARING]

05:17.499 --> 05:19.333
<i>♪ </i>

05:19.358 --> 05:21.424
Sorry, yes, I understand.
Step back.

05:21.449 --> 05:22.806
Step back, ma'am.

05:22.831 --> 05:24.393
We'll let you know as soon as possible.

05:24.418 --> 05:26.504
All right, people, the ED
is officially on bypass.

05:26.529 --> 05:29.402
Lock it down. Nothing comes in or out.

05:29.427 --> 05:31.030
Keep your eyes open for a woman,

05:31.055 --> 05:32.889
probably in scrubs, with an infant.

05:32.914 --> 05:34.348
Doris, triage the waiting room.

05:34.373 --> 05:35.855
Let's clear out any rooms we can.

05:35.880 --> 05:37.308
And cycle in the patients with
the most immediate needs.

05:37.333 --> 05:38.614
Got it.

05:38.803 --> 05:41.695
Monique, I want an inventory
of our drugs, blood products,

05:41.720 --> 05:43.220
all critical supplies.

05:43.245 --> 05:45.276
We need to be ready to make do
with what we've got on hand.

05:45.301 --> 05:46.052
Copy.

05:46.077 --> 05:48.049
The cops should've
stopped you. We're on bypass.

05:48.074 --> 05:49.835
We're not leaving.
This guy could die.

05:49.860 --> 05:52.092
Earl, we're not gonna let
this man bleed to death.

05:52.117 --> 05:53.847
Let him in. It's on me.

05:53.872 --> 05:56.231
Come on, let's go. Dr. Choi?

05:56.256 --> 05:57.779
- Right here.
- You're going to Baghdad.

05:57.804 --> 05:59.085
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

05:59.110 --> 06:01.580
Tim Vance, 30-year-old male.
Bar fight.

06:01.605 --> 06:03.334
Took a long blade to his left chest.

06:03.359 --> 06:05.940
Heart rate, 120. BP, 92 over 58.

06:05.965 --> 06:07.833
He stabbed me
over a game of pool.

06:07.858 --> 06:09.939
All right, save your breath.

06:10.788 --> 06:12.660
Let's transfer.

06:13.516 --> 06:16.307
On my count. Ready, one, two, three.

06:16.332 --> 06:18.286
[GROANS]

06:18.575 --> 06:25.086
<i>♪ </i>

06:25.291 --> 06:27.058
All right,
no breath sounds on the left.

06:27.082 --> 06:28.825
- Hand me the ultrasound.
<i>- Code Pink...</i>

06:28.850 --> 06:32.335
The Code Pink could be
the baby I treated.

06:32.360 --> 06:33.923
Man...

06:34.185 --> 06:36.738
<i>♪ </i>

06:36.967 --> 06:38.824
He's got a large pericardial effusion.

06:38.849 --> 06:40.268
Blood's pooling around the heart.

06:40.293 --> 06:41.277
BP's falling!

06:41.302 --> 06:42.722
Tamponade's compressing
the heart.

06:42.747 --> 06:44.757
He's bradying down. Start bagging.
Page Dr. Rhodes.

06:44.782 --> 06:47.486
He's not in the hospital.
Big CT event off campus.

06:47.511 --> 06:49.043
They're not gonna let him
in 'cause of the lockdown.

06:49.068 --> 06:50.963
- Get me another surgeon.
- Dr. Latham's in surgery,

06:50.988 --> 06:53.069
and the Trauma service is up
in the O.R. on another case.

06:53.094 --> 06:54.814
Then splash prep his left
chest and hand me a knife.

06:54.839 --> 06:56.186
I gotta open him up now.

06:56.385 --> 07:00.748
<i>♪ </i>

07:00.953 --> 07:03.755
[LAID-BACK PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

07:03.780 --> 07:05.116
- Dr. Rhodes.
- Morning.

07:05.141 --> 07:06.479
Morning.
You know my husband, Larry.

07:06.504 --> 07:07.456
Larry, good to see you.

07:07.481 --> 07:09.449
He's always dragging me
to these things.

07:09.474 --> 07:11.401
I'm an introvert. I hate them.

07:11.426 --> 07:12.931
I am completely with you there.

07:12.956 --> 07:14.882
Yes, well, there are
a lot of checkbooks here,

07:14.907 --> 07:17.151
and their owners would like
to meet our rising star,

07:17.176 --> 07:20.578
so please... go and schmooze.

07:20.603 --> 07:22.881
[CHUCKLING] Ah.

07:22.906 --> 07:24.774
Dad.

07:24.837 --> 07:27.142
Were your ears burning?
We were just talking about you.

07:27.167 --> 07:28.537
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

07:28.562 --> 07:30.533
I told Dr. Bekker how
your mother and I knew,

07:30.558 --> 07:32.137
even when you were just a little boy,

07:32.162 --> 07:33.794
how you'd be a surgeon.

07:34.125 --> 07:37.894
Do you remember when that dog
got ahold of your Teddy Ruxpin?

07:38.203 --> 07:40.337
He sewed that little thing together.

07:40.426 --> 07:42.467
You had a Teddy Ruxpin?

07:42.492 --> 07:44.889
I wouldn't believe
everything my father tells you.

07:45.008 --> 07:46.933
Oh, Connor's always
been uncomfortable

07:46.958 --> 07:48.993
with anything that smelled of praise.

07:49.018 --> 07:50.917
That's funny,
I never noticed that.

07:51.606 --> 07:53.206
I'm gonna go get some breakfast.

07:53.231 --> 07:54.898
Try the avocado toast.

07:54.923 --> 07:57.191
<i>♪ </i>

07:57.216 --> 07:59.383
We are having a trunk show
next week.

07:59.408 --> 08:02.510
Loro Piana. I would love it
if you'd come as my guest.

08:02.535 --> 08:04.162
I'd love to.

08:04.187 --> 08:07.125
Ava...
hospital's on lockdown.

08:07.150 --> 08:09.012
<i>♪ </i>

08:09.053 --> 08:10.687
Uh-huh. Uh-huh.

08:10.712 --> 08:12.697
Dr. Reese, Goodwin needs us upstairs

08:12.722 --> 08:14.397
to consult on that Code Pink.

08:14.422 --> 08:16.064
On the way.

08:17.965 --> 08:21.000
[KEYBOARD CLACKING]

08:24.196 --> 08:25.930
Hey.

08:25.955 --> 08:27.956
Hey.

08:28.929 --> 08:31.068
<i>Code Pink. Code Pink.</i>

08:31.093 --> 08:32.581
<i>All hospital personnel,</i>

08:32.606 --> 08:34.352
<i>please report to your
designated stations.</i>

08:34.378 --> 08:36.067
It was a baby that I treated.

08:36.092 --> 08:38.051
Oh, God.

08:38.663 --> 08:40.986
Patient got in
just under the wire.

08:43.346 --> 08:46.109
Both of you, please.

08:50.103 --> 08:51.704
- [KNOCKS ON WALL]
- Good morning.

08:51.738 --> 08:53.550
I'm Dr. Halstead. This is Dr. Manning.

08:53.575 --> 08:54.885
- Hi.
- Hello.

08:54.910 --> 08:57.447
Mr. Taylor, I see you're
being treated for lymphoma.

08:57.472 --> 08:58.722
That's right.

08:58.747 --> 09:00.748
He's had multiple rounds
of chemo.

09:00.831 --> 09:02.802
So, what brings you in today?

09:03.098 --> 09:06.429
[SIGHS] Woke up this morning,
could hardly breathe.

09:06.453 --> 09:08.676
Our oncologist at East Mercy
said to come here

09:08.701 --> 09:09.925
since it's closer.

09:09.950 --> 09:11.743
Well, it's a good thing
that you did.

09:11.768 --> 09:14.390
Uh, let's get a chest X-ray,
CBC, coags, and a d-dimer,

09:14.415 --> 09:16.973
and also, call over to East
Mercy for his records, okay?

09:16.998 --> 09:17.666
Thank you.

09:17.691 --> 09:19.402
Just try to relax,
Mr. Taylor.

09:19.427 --> 09:21.036
We're gonna run these
tests and sort this out.

09:21.061 --> 09:22.455
- Okay.
- We'll be back shortly.

09:22.480 --> 09:23.682
Thanks.

09:23.848 --> 09:26.036
Let's hope he's just got
a little bug.

09:26.061 --> 09:28.229
Yeah.
Nat...

09:31.037 --> 09:33.038
I can't stand this. We gotta talk.

09:33.063 --> 09:34.682
I know.

09:34.912 --> 09:36.512
Come over tonight.

09:36.537 --> 09:39.064
<i>[DISQUIETING MUSIC]</i>

09:39.089 --> 09:40.723
<i>♪ </i>

09:40.748 --> 09:42.390
We reviewed
all the security cam footage.

09:42.415 --> 09:44.806
No one left the hospital
with the infant.

09:44.831 --> 09:48.198
So he and his abductor
are still on the premises?

09:48.223 --> 09:49.211
We think so.

09:49.236 --> 09:51.344
We would've gotten a ping from
the abductor's ID bracelet

09:51.369 --> 09:53.167
if the abductor had
tried to exit with him.

09:53.192 --> 09:55.606
Dr. Charles,
from your experience,

09:55.631 --> 09:58.112
what kind of person do you
think we're looking for?

09:58.188 --> 09:59.953
In a majority of these cases,

09:59.978 --> 10:02.591
the abductor is a woman
of child-bearing age,

10:02.616 --> 10:04.957
who is either infertile

10:04.982 --> 10:06.820
or has experienced fetal loss.

10:07.103 --> 10:09.135
Um, they're distraught and
determined one way or the other

10:09.160 --> 10:10.301
to have a baby of their own.

10:10.326 --> 10:12.733
Then maybe she's not likely
to hurt him.

10:12.818 --> 10:15.536
Not if wanting a child
is what's driving her.

10:15.690 --> 10:17.866
But what if that's
not what's driving her?

10:17.891 --> 10:19.863
What if she's someone who
enjoys causing other's pain,

10:19.888 --> 10:22.084
a person without a conscience?

10:22.453 --> 10:23.693
I mean, it's possible,

10:23.718 --> 10:25.487
and if someone like that
gets backed into a corner,

10:25.512 --> 10:28.081
there's no telling how she might react.

10:28.612 --> 10:31.036
This person knew
where the PICU was.

10:31.061 --> 10:32.873
Could very well have
been a patient here.

10:32.898 --> 10:35.613
I think we should
compile a list of women

10:35.638 --> 10:37.272
who have experienced birth trauma here

10:37.306 --> 10:38.773
in the last six months.

10:38.807 --> 10:41.586
All right, and I think
it's a good idea for you

10:41.611 --> 10:44.946
to assign a psychiatrist
to each search team,

10:44.971 --> 10:48.440
help defuse any situation where
the baby may be at risk.

10:48.523 --> 10:50.090
Let's get started.

10:50.218 --> 10:52.947
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

10:53.089 --> 10:54.602
Daniel...

10:55.660 --> 10:57.160
we've got to find this baby.

10:57.656 --> 11:01.959
<i>♪ </i>

11:03.861 --> 11:06.392
Your patient has
a large mediastinal mass

11:06.417 --> 11:08.757
with what looks like positive
nodes throughout his chest.

11:08.782 --> 11:10.813
It's compressing his lungs
and all his major vessels.

11:10.838 --> 11:12.205
That's why he's so short of breath.

11:12.239 --> 11:13.406
Okay, so, what's next?

11:13.431 --> 11:15.199
Surgery? Another round of chemo?

11:15.224 --> 11:17.449
A tumor this large?
Even with chemotherapy,

11:17.474 --> 11:19.385
it wouldn't shrink to an operable size.

11:19.410 --> 11:20.771
Then what?

11:20.906 --> 11:22.379
Um, from his medical records,

11:22.404 --> 11:24.556
it looks like he's had a
solid treatment history.

11:24.581 --> 11:27.550
Unfortunately, we've reached
the limits of what we can do.

11:27.584 --> 11:29.763
So that's it?
We're giving up?

11:29.788 --> 11:31.723
No, there... there has to be
something else we can do.

11:31.757 --> 11:33.274
- Uh...
- My advice?

11:33.299 --> 11:35.460
The sooner you tell Mr. Taylor
and his wife the prognosis,

11:35.485 --> 11:36.780
the better.

11:36.805 --> 11:39.106
It'll give them a chance
to find some closure.

11:44.707 --> 11:46.708
[KNOCKING ON WALL]

11:46.733 --> 11:48.090
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:48.115 --> 11:49.824
I got your CT results.

11:49.849 --> 11:51.752
In addition to your rib injury,

11:51.777 --> 11:54.750
you also have a compression
fracture of your L2.

11:54.775 --> 11:56.405
That's a vertebrae in your lower back.

11:56.430 --> 11:58.035
Now, it's not serious.

11:58.060 --> 11:59.639
- Doesn't require surgery...
- [EXHALES]

11:59.664 --> 12:02.002
But because of the chest tube
and the fractures,

12:02.027 --> 12:04.707
we wanna keep you in the
hospital for a couple of days.

12:04.732 --> 12:05.829
Once we get you upstairs,

12:05.854 --> 12:07.721
we'll start you on a
pain-management regimen

12:07.782 --> 12:09.804
and fit you for a brace, okay?

12:09.941 --> 12:13.135
- [EXHALES]
- Thank you, Dr. Sexton.

12:17.305 --> 12:19.244
How much time do I have?

12:19.853 --> 12:21.587
Hard to say.

12:21.747 --> 12:23.817
A few weeks, maybe less.

12:23.842 --> 12:25.911
Oh, my God.

12:26.555 --> 12:28.311
I am so sorry.

12:28.336 --> 12:31.305
<i>[SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

12:31.531 --> 12:33.532
<i>♪ </i>

12:33.714 --> 12:36.708
We can have a hospice nurse
come in and talk to you.

12:36.757 --> 12:38.778
[BREATHING SHAKILY] A hospice?

12:38.803 --> 12:40.380
I know...

12:40.472 --> 12:42.306
but hospice will provide your husband

12:42.331 --> 12:45.623
with the best quality of life
in the time that remains.

12:46.100 --> 12:49.013
I always said
I wanted to die at home.

12:49.555 --> 12:51.971
Looks like I'll get my wish.

12:52.551 --> 12:54.929
It'll be all right, Bev.

12:55.758 --> 12:58.026
Call the kids, have them come out.

12:58.343 --> 13:03.765
<i>♪ </i>

13:04.804 --> 13:06.718
How soon can we leave?

13:07.502 --> 13:11.038
Unfortunately, the hospital
is under lockdown currently,

13:11.072 --> 13:12.290
due to a security issue.

13:12.314 --> 13:13.740
No one is allowed in or out.

13:13.775 --> 13:15.543
But we can start
your discharge paperwork,

13:15.577 --> 13:17.311
and as soon as the lockdown is lifted,

13:17.345 --> 13:19.030
you'll be able to go home.

13:20.017 --> 13:21.517
Thank you.

13:21.542 --> 13:23.143
[SNIFFLING]

13:23.351 --> 13:27.660
<i>♪ </i>

13:28.495 --> 13:30.176
It's okay.

13:30.306 --> 13:31.969
<i>♪ </i>

13:32.082 --> 13:34.233
[RIB SPREADER TICKING]

13:34.333 --> 13:35.967
Heart rate's down to 80.

13:35.992 --> 13:37.347
All right...

13:37.463 --> 13:39.364
I'm gonna release the tamponade.

13:39.438 --> 13:40.866
Give me some suction.

13:41.127 --> 13:43.590
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

13:43.981 --> 13:46.232
<i>♪ </i>

13:46.613 --> 13:48.188
Numbers are still in the tank.

13:48.213 --> 13:49.961
Because he was stabbed
in the heart. He needs blood.

13:49.986 --> 13:51.769
I don't care where he
is, get me Connor.

13:51.794 --> 13:53.829
Just prepare
an innocuous press release,

13:53.863 --> 13:55.930
and then let me know the
second we find that baby.

13:55.955 --> 13:58.604
[PHONE BEEPING, TRILLS]

13:58.765 --> 14:00.098
<i>Dr. Rhodes.</i>

14:00.124 --> 14:01.649
<i>Connor, I need your help, buddy.</i>

14:01.724 --> 14:03.969
Yeah, okay. Ava.

14:04.719 --> 14:07.749
[ELEVATOR DINGING]

14:08.988 --> 14:11.316
Surgical suites one and three
aren't in use.

14:11.341 --> 14:13.054
You check those, we'll cover the rest.

14:13.079 --> 14:15.013
<i>Code Pink. Code Pink.</i>

14:15.038 --> 14:16.505
<i>All hospital personnel,</i>

14:16.530 --> 14:18.829
<i>please report to your
designated stations.</i>

14:19.277 --> 14:20.829
Clear.

14:21.675 --> 14:24.869
So, your description
of our attacker

14:24.894 --> 14:26.862
is someone possibly
without a conscience.

14:26.896 --> 14:29.378
I'm just curious, what led you to that?

14:29.498 --> 14:30.824
There have been
a number of cases

14:30.849 --> 14:32.250
of women murdering children:

14:32.275 --> 14:34.376
Diane Downs, Susan Smith.

14:34.401 --> 14:35.802
I don't really see
the comparison, though.

14:35.827 --> 14:37.394
I mean, neither of those women

14:37.419 --> 14:39.309
abducted a baby from a hospital.

14:39.334 --> 14:40.605
You're just speculating too.

14:40.630 --> 14:41.992
We don't know who we're dealing with.

14:42.017 --> 14:43.632
There's no guarantee
she's some bereft mother

14:43.657 --> 14:44.655
who's lost a child.

14:44.680 --> 14:46.165
For all we know, she could be a...

14:46.409 --> 14:47.962
A psychopath?

14:50.223 --> 14:52.945
Dr. Charles, this has
nothing to do with my father.

14:53.214 --> 14:55.433
And just because my opinion
is different from yours

14:55.458 --> 14:58.252
- doesn't make it biased.
- All clear.

15:02.862 --> 15:05.962
Will, I've been doing
research on Gary's cancer,

15:05.987 --> 15:08.162
and I found a case where a combination

15:08.187 --> 15:09.959
of bleomycin, etoposide, and cisplatin

15:09.984 --> 15:12.378
rapidly shrank germ cell tumors,

15:12.403 --> 15:13.811
so I called my oncologist friend,

15:13.836 --> 15:15.930
who said it was anecdotal but possible.

15:16.621 --> 15:18.265
Anecdotal?

15:18.290 --> 15:19.677
There haven't been any studies,

15:19.702 --> 15:21.336
and it's not approved by the FDA.

15:21.484 --> 15:24.007
So, you're proposing
we use these drugs off-label?

15:24.032 --> 15:25.899
Will, the man is terminally ill.

15:25.924 --> 15:28.387
Yes... and I don't wanna
speed up that process,

15:28.412 --> 15:30.730
or cause him any unnecessary suffering.

15:30.755 --> 15:32.230
Well, I think
it's worth the risk.

15:32.255 --> 15:33.943
I'm sorry, I don't.

15:34.388 --> 15:36.352
What happened to you?

15:36.842 --> 15:39.879
You used to go to any length
to try and save someone.

15:39.904 --> 15:41.431
Yeah, and it never ended well.

15:41.456 --> 15:43.699
I also have a larger
responsibility now.

15:43.724 --> 15:45.839
- Because you're an Attending?
- That's right.

15:46.483 --> 15:48.225
So I don't get a say?

15:48.547 --> 15:50.181
I'm sorry, in this case, no.

15:50.206 --> 15:52.300
What you're suggesting is bad medicine.

15:52.430 --> 15:54.152
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

15:54.177 --> 15:55.544
Okay.

15:55.885 --> 16:01.041
<i>♪ </i>

16:01.445 --> 16:03.440
All right, give me
a view of the medial side

16:03.465 --> 16:05.141
of the left ventricle.

16:05.166 --> 16:06.435
<i>Yeah, good.</i>

16:06.460 --> 16:08.194
Uh, now, Ethan, you're
gonna remove your finger,

16:08.273 --> 16:10.122
and once you get the stapler in place,

16:10.147 --> 16:12.348
you're gonna close laterally
across the opening.

16:12.395 --> 16:14.563
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

16:14.588 --> 16:16.081
I can't get
the stapler in place.

16:16.106 --> 16:17.388
It's a moving target.

16:17.413 --> 16:19.707
- Keep trying.
- [RIB SPREADER TICKING]

16:19.732 --> 16:21.228
Got it. Staple's in.

16:21.268 --> 16:23.230
Good.

16:23.255 --> 16:25.123
<i>No. No, wait,
this isn't working.</i>

16:25.148 --> 16:26.840
<i>Every time I get a staple in, it tears,</i>

16:26.865 --> 16:28.525
<i>- making the hole even bigger.
- All right, here.</i>

16:28.550 --> 16:30.173
- What are you doing?
- I gotta get in there.

16:30.198 --> 16:31.877
The hospital's on lockdown.
They won't let you in.

16:31.902 --> 16:33.950
I have to try.
Help Ethan get him stabilized.

16:34.037 --> 16:35.766
<i>♪ </i>

16:35.791 --> 16:38.109
All right, Dr. Choi,
let's see if I can keep you

16:38.134 --> 16:39.916
<i>from killing this patient.</i>

16:40.201 --> 16:42.780
You understand
this is experimental?

16:42.979 --> 16:44.914
I can't guarantee it'll have any effect

16:44.939 --> 16:46.973
on Mr. Taylor's cancer.

16:47.103 --> 16:48.891
It might even be harmful.

16:49.093 --> 16:50.737
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

16:50.868 --> 16:52.391
We understand.

16:52.416 --> 16:54.573
And do I have your permission?

16:55.748 --> 16:57.402
Yes.

16:57.950 --> 17:00.763
Please. Go ahead.

17:00.788 --> 17:02.340
Okay.

17:02.718 --> 17:09.758
<i>♪ </i>

17:11.000 --> 17:17.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

17:38.984 --> 17:40.835
Sorry, folks, as soon as
the lockdown is lifted,

17:40.860 --> 17:42.151
you'll all get to see a doctor.

17:42.176 --> 17:44.090
So what? I'm just supposed
to wait here bleeding?

17:44.115 --> 17:45.438
Got no choice, ma'am.
If you're worried,

17:45.463 --> 17:47.211
Lakeshore Memorial's only a mile away.

17:47.236 --> 17:48.579
Sir, gotta stop you there.

17:48.604 --> 17:51.659
Look, I am a doctor
on staff here, all right?

17:51.684 --> 17:53.079
Sorry, can't let you in.

17:53.104 --> 17:54.637
There is a man
in the emergency room

17:54.662 --> 17:56.665
- with a stab wound in his heart.
- Sorry.

17:56.690 --> 17:58.958
If I don't get in there,
he's gonna die.

17:59.127 --> 18:00.698
Not my call.

18:00.967 --> 18:03.702
I wish I could let you in,
but it's not up to me.

18:03.727 --> 18:05.552
- Fine.
- I will let you in,

18:05.577 --> 18:08.266
- as soon as the lockdown is...
- Earl, I need to get in there.

18:08.291 --> 18:10.592
Can you help me out?

18:10.861 --> 18:12.530
Come with me.

18:15.026 --> 18:17.027
I found this tunnel
when we were reviewing

18:17.052 --> 18:20.476
the hospital's emergency
evacuation plan.

18:20.621 --> 18:22.889
Apparently, it was
used to ferry patients

18:22.914 --> 18:25.850
and supplies between buildings.

18:26.060 --> 18:28.968
But once they put in the
over-street walkways,

18:28.993 --> 18:30.651
it was decommissioned.

18:30.676 --> 18:32.746
Here's your way in.

18:34.766 --> 18:37.380
When you come to the
fork, stay to the right.

18:37.405 --> 18:40.170
At the end of the tunnel,
you'll find a series of doors.

18:40.195 --> 18:41.844
Take the first one on the right.

18:41.869 --> 18:43.637
That'll put you inside the hospital.

18:43.662 --> 18:44.627
All right, thanks, Earl.

18:44.652 --> 18:46.776
Oh, and you...
You might need this.

18:47.870 --> 18:50.976
Anyone asks, it wasn't me who told you.

18:51.001 --> 18:52.368
You got it.

18:52.393 --> 18:55.362
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

18:55.972 --> 19:03.045
<i>♪ </i>

19:32.942 --> 19:35.848
- How's she doing?
- Um, sleeping.

19:35.873 --> 19:38.704
Good. We're still waiting
for a room to open.

19:38.729 --> 19:40.496
I'm transferring another patient now,

19:40.521 --> 19:42.609
but Jill's next in line.

19:42.762 --> 19:44.429
Hopefully won't be much longer.

19:50.635 --> 19:53.250
Dr. Manning, can I see you?

19:53.460 --> 19:55.507
Please excuse me.

20:00.732 --> 20:02.266
- You gave him those drugs?
- Mm-hmm.

20:02.291 --> 20:04.469
I told you not to,
and you did it anyway.

20:04.494 --> 20:05.961
His wife wanted
to give 'em a try.

20:05.996 --> 20:07.530
You shouldn't have
even suggested it.

20:07.564 --> 20:09.565
She deserved a choice.

20:09.599 --> 20:12.134
You went behind my back.
I can't believe you did that.

20:12.169 --> 20:14.703
- You wouldn't listen to me.
- I did listen to you.

20:14.738 --> 20:16.220
<i>♪ </i>

20:16.245 --> 20:18.550
I just hope you haven't put a
nail in this man's coffin.

20:18.855 --> 20:25.928
<i>♪ </i>

20:29.370 --> 20:32.564
- [PHONE RINGING]
- Cole here.

20:32.589 --> 20:35.856
We just got a ping
off the baby's ID bracelet.

20:36.259 --> 20:38.727
- She used an emergency exit
STAIRWELL: East Wing.

20:38.762 --> 20:40.896
<i>♪ </i>

20:40.931 --> 20:42.698
Wait...

20:42.732 --> 20:46.275
<i>♪ </i>

20:46.300 --> 20:48.180
- "Zachary Womack."
- They were here.

20:48.205 --> 20:49.799
She cut off his bracelet.

20:49.824 --> 20:51.084
She knew the signal
would bring us here.

20:51.109 --> 20:52.676
She's playing a game with us.

20:52.701 --> 20:54.570
His IV.

20:54.595 --> 20:56.797
He's not getting his
antibiotics anymore.

20:56.980 --> 21:03.285
<i>♪ </i>

21:03.436 --> 21:05.546
<i>Ah, come on.</i>

21:07.564 --> 21:09.058
I still can't get it in.

21:09.092 --> 21:11.026
Get me a closer look
at the hole.

21:13.061 --> 21:14.928
<i>Here's what I want you to do:</i>

21:15.065 --> 21:17.111
Get two Allis clamps...

21:18.969 --> 21:20.536
Here.

21:20.570 --> 21:22.905
I want you to clamp on
either side of the hole.

21:30.747 --> 21:33.148
- Ready.
- Okay, April,

21:33.183 --> 21:34.950
you're going to take hold of the clamps

21:34.985 --> 21:36.886
<i>- and lift the heart.
- 'Kay.</i>

21:36.911 --> 21:38.278
As soon as she does,

21:38.303 --> 21:39.835
Dr. Choi, you'll remove your finger

21:39.860 --> 21:41.233
and see if you can get the staple in

21:41.258 --> 21:42.297
while it's elevated.

21:42.322 --> 21:44.122
<i>- Got it?
- Copy.</i>

21:44.157 --> 21:47.757
<i>Here we go.
One, two, three, lift.</i>

21:50.038 --> 21:52.006
It's in. It's working.

21:52.031 --> 21:54.200
Well done.

21:54.460 --> 21:56.728
Ava... Ava,
he's still bleeding.

21:56.753 --> 21:58.548
Give me suction.

21:59.290 --> 22:01.001
He's hypotensive!

22:01.026 --> 22:03.107
Dr. Choi, I need you to snake
your hand around the heart.

22:03.132 --> 22:04.890
What do you feel?

22:05.886 --> 22:07.553
He's got a hole in the backside.

22:07.578 --> 22:09.863
<i>The knife went
through and through.</i>

22:09.888 --> 22:11.516
<i>Looks like you have more work to do.</i>

22:11.541 --> 22:13.352
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

22:13.469 --> 22:16.529
- What's happening?
- He's in v-fib.

22:17.079 --> 22:18.890
No pulse.
Monique, start bagging.

22:18.915 --> 22:20.818
Doris, get on his chest.

22:21.011 --> 22:24.771
<i>♪ </i>

22:24.959 --> 22:27.453
Charge to 150. Clear.

22:27.478 --> 22:30.180
[MONITOR BEEPING]

22:30.554 --> 22:31.921
Still in v-fib.

22:31.946 --> 22:34.280
Monique,
push 1 milligram of epi.

22:34.483 --> 22:36.720
- Doris, get back on his chest.
- I got it.

22:36.935 --> 22:38.801
<i>♪ </i>

22:39.049 --> 22:40.920
Hold compressions.

22:41.216 --> 22:42.950
Clear.

22:42.992 --> 22:45.126
<i>♪ </i>

22:45.318 --> 22:46.579
No pulse.

22:46.604 --> 22:48.609
Monique, another milligram
of epi and atropine.

22:48.821 --> 22:55.894
<i>♪ </i>

22:59.332 --> 23:01.113
[SIGHS]

23:01.138 --> 23:03.329
<i>♪ </i>

23:03.354 --> 23:05.029
Natalie...

23:05.054 --> 23:12.027
<i>♪ </i>

23:12.052 --> 23:14.248
Natalie... he's gone.

23:14.273 --> 23:17.078
[SOBBING] My Gary...

23:17.103 --> 23:19.711
<i>[SOMBER MUSIC]</i>

23:20.131 --> 23:21.699
<i>♪ </i>

23:21.724 --> 23:24.040
Time of death: 14:30.

23:24.065 --> 23:27.125
[SNIFFLES] I'm sorry.
I'm so sorry.

23:27.150 --> 23:32.342
<i>♪ </i>

23:32.532 --> 23:35.268
- Just don't even say it.
- Nat...

23:35.293 --> 23:38.457
Off-label meds.
Did I kill him?

23:38.782 --> 23:41.033
- The man was dying.
- I shouldn't have done it.

23:41.058 --> 23:42.374
[SOBS]

23:42.469 --> 23:46.553
<i>♪ </i>

23:47.039 --> 23:50.007
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

23:50.574 --> 23:57.613
<i>♪ </i>

24:07.815 --> 24:10.509
[GRUNTING]

24:11.194 --> 24:18.044
<i>♪ </i>

24:18.248 --> 24:19.973
Uh, yeah, sorry.

24:20.354 --> 24:23.709
<i>♪ </i>

24:23.879 --> 24:27.147
Help! There's something wrong
with my daughter.

24:27.383 --> 24:29.905
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

24:30.101 --> 24:31.601
What's happening?

24:31.626 --> 24:34.270
Her vocal chords are
spasming, blocking airflow.

24:34.295 --> 24:36.160
Help her!

24:36.185 --> 24:38.598
This is Noah's patient.
Where is he?

24:38.623 --> 24:40.720
He had to take
a patient upstairs.

24:41.070 --> 24:42.935
Dr. Choi, we need some help over here.

24:42.960 --> 24:46.081
- I'm a little busy!
- Ay-yai-yai-yah.

24:46.294 --> 24:49.384
[VALVE HISSING]

24:49.414 --> 24:51.286
- We need to intubate.
- Maggie...

24:51.311 --> 24:52.724
20 of etomidate, 10 of sux.

24:52.749 --> 24:55.839
Maggie...
we need a doctor.

24:56.278 --> 24:57.752
Now.

24:57.891 --> 24:59.829
<i>♪ </i>

24:59.854 --> 25:01.613
Okay, sweetie.

25:01.935 --> 25:09.008
<i>♪ </i>

25:19.661 --> 25:21.228
It's too tight.

25:21.253 --> 25:23.479
I can't get past the vocal chords.

25:23.504 --> 25:26.106
She's down to 87.
We need a doctor.

25:26.131 --> 25:27.498
Oh, God.

25:27.675 --> 25:30.584
<i>♪ </i>

25:31.031 --> 25:32.560
I'll crich her.

25:32.585 --> 25:35.248
Are you crazy?
You can't do that.

25:35.460 --> 25:37.862
Doris, give me a scalpel.

25:37.887 --> 25:39.707
You're not allowed.
It's gotta be a doctor.

25:39.732 --> 25:41.467
Help her!

25:41.949 --> 25:43.498
Give me the scalpel, Doris.

25:43.648 --> 25:50.720
<i>♪ </i>

25:54.130 --> 25:57.099
[SOBBING]

25:58.015 --> 26:05.088
<i>♪ </i>

26:06.302 --> 26:08.136
I'm in. Bag her.

26:08.161 --> 26:10.469
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

26:10.604 --> 26:12.095
Got it.

26:13.073 --> 26:15.074
Sats are coming back up.

26:15.585 --> 26:21.357
<i>♪ </i>

26:22.999 --> 26:25.500
He's bradying down.

26:25.534 --> 26:28.837
- [GRUNTS] I can't reach it.
- Keep trying.

26:28.871 --> 26:30.839
Heart rate's dropping.

26:30.873 --> 26:32.507
Where are we?

26:32.753 --> 26:34.120
It's about time.

26:34.145 --> 26:36.311
Hole backside of his left ventricle.

26:36.945 --> 26:38.713
<i>Connor, here's what's happening:</i>

26:38.738 --> 26:40.355
Whenever they elevate the
heart to make the repair,

26:40.380 --> 26:42.433
it cuts off his venous return.

26:44.010 --> 26:45.711
Okay, get me two bags of saline.

26:45.736 --> 26:48.913
April, load up a 2-0 prolene
on a long needle driver.

26:49.822 --> 26:52.000
- How'd you get in here?
- Long story.

26:52.025 --> 26:54.061
On my count, I want you to
roll him onto his side.

26:54.086 --> 26:55.880
One, two, three.

26:55.905 --> 26:58.818
Up... and down.

27:00.446 --> 27:03.081
All right, Ethan, when I tell you,

27:03.106 --> 27:05.109
I want you to remove your finger,

27:05.134 --> 27:06.258
and I'm gonna replace it with mine.

27:06.283 --> 27:07.951
Ready and go.

27:07.976 --> 27:10.971
Okay, I'm gonna try to access the hole

27:10.996 --> 27:12.416
from this angle.

27:12.441 --> 27:14.981
Careful,
he bradies down quickly.

27:21.793 --> 27:23.827
All right, stitch is in.

27:23.862 --> 27:25.562
That should temporize
the bleed long enough

27:25.597 --> 27:26.926
to get him up to the O.R.

27:26.951 --> 27:28.452
Let's go.

27:28.496 --> 27:30.263
[PHONE BEEPS]

27:30.509 --> 27:33.372
Dr. Bekker, you are amazing.

27:33.467 --> 27:35.167
Thank you.

27:46.714 --> 27:49.382
Dr. Halstead,
Dr. Ray tells me

27:49.407 --> 27:52.076
off-label meds were
given to that patient.

27:52.101 --> 27:55.170
Bleomycin,
etoposide, and cisplatin.

27:55.195 --> 27:57.358
- For lymphoma?
- I know.

27:57.383 --> 27:59.184
But the patient died
within hours

27:59.209 --> 28:01.412
after the drugs were administered.

28:01.437 --> 28:03.171
Adverse drug reaction.

28:03.196 --> 28:05.132
We could get sued for this.

28:05.157 --> 28:07.492
Where is Dr. Manning?

28:07.653 --> 28:10.555
Ms. Goodwin, the chart,
it's not correct.

28:10.789 --> 28:12.824
Dr. Manning didn't prescribe the drugs.

28:12.858 --> 28:15.233
- It was me.
- You?

28:15.439 --> 28:17.373
I found some anecdotal evidence

28:17.398 --> 28:19.534
that supported the
efficacy of that cocktail.

28:20.345 --> 28:22.193
Thought we had nothing to lose.

28:22.218 --> 28:24.386
Dr. Halstead, I had hoped

28:24.411 --> 28:26.780
that you had outgrown
your recklessness.

28:27.182 --> 28:28.851
Clearly, you haven't.

28:29.285 --> 28:30.886
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

28:31.076 --> 28:34.053
I'm referring this to the
disciplinary committee.

28:34.613 --> 28:41.619
<i>♪ </i>

28:47.053 --> 28:49.870
Hey, uh, my patient
in Treatment Two,

28:49.895 --> 28:51.187
- who criched her?
- I did.

28:51.212 --> 28:53.531
- What?
- You criched a patient?

28:53.954 --> 28:56.179
She was in laryngospasm,
you weren't available,

28:56.204 --> 28:58.044
and all my other doctors were tied up.

28:58.069 --> 28:59.474
A nurse cannot crich.

28:59.499 --> 29:01.130
You should've waited for a doctor.

29:01.155 --> 29:02.499
- She would've died.
- And you could've killed her.

29:02.524 --> 29:03.785
- Noah...
- What?

29:03.810 --> 29:05.977
Maggie's been nursing since
before you started shaving.

29:06.002 --> 29:07.205
So what?
It's against the rules.

29:07.230 --> 29:08.827
She's seen a crich
done 1,000 times.

29:08.852 --> 29:10.528
- Okay.
- Back off.

29:10.553 --> 29:13.657
Please, we need a doctor.
She's waking up.

29:14.064 --> 29:16.948
Jill? Honey? Can you hear me?

29:16.973 --> 29:19.545
<i>[TENSE MUSIC]</i>

29:19.570 --> 29:21.136
What's wrong with her eye?

29:21.161 --> 29:23.102
She's got a left-sided
facial droop.

29:23.127 --> 29:24.396
I think she might've had a stroke.

29:24.421 --> 29:25.797
<i>♪ </i>

29:25.822 --> 29:27.662
All right, we need to get
her up for a head CT now.

29:27.686 --> 29:28.953
- Let's go.
- Get ready to bag her.

29:28.979 --> 29:31.147
- On it.
- One, two, three.

29:31.391 --> 29:34.360
[SOBBING]

29:34.606 --> 29:41.679
<i>♪ </i>

29:51.547 --> 29:54.055
Hey...
you told Dr. Ray

29:54.080 --> 29:56.679
that you prescribed Gary's meds?

30:03.928 --> 30:06.270
- It's no big deal.
- Yes, it is.

30:06.295 --> 30:08.943
I own my mistakes, not you.

30:08.968 --> 30:10.735
I feel terrible that Gary might've died

30:10.760 --> 30:11.893
because of those drugs,

30:11.918 --> 30:14.320
but I am the one responsible, okay?

30:14.345 --> 30:16.365
You do not need to protect me.

30:16.390 --> 30:17.755
- I know that.
- Do you?

30:17.780 --> 30:18.939
Do you know that?

30:18.964 --> 30:21.119
Natalie, you are
already miserable.

30:21.177 --> 30:23.713
I didn't want you to have
to deal with all this.

30:23.849 --> 30:25.597
Besides, I'm the Attending.

30:25.622 --> 30:27.018
Ultimately, it's my responsibility.

30:27.043 --> 30:29.578
Oh, my... come off it.

30:29.603 --> 30:32.204
Would you have done the same
thing for Ethan or for Noah?

30:32.229 --> 30:33.526
No, because they're men.

30:33.551 --> 30:35.051
They can take care of themselves.

30:35.076 --> 30:38.462
But not me. I'm just a
helpless little girl.

30:44.408 --> 30:46.226
I have some news.

30:46.251 --> 30:49.324
Security compiled a
list of former patients

30:49.349 --> 30:51.961
who fit the profile of our abductor,

30:51.986 --> 30:53.961
then cross-referenced them

30:53.986 --> 30:56.479
against today's visitors log.

30:56.504 --> 30:58.580
Turns out, we got a hit.

30:58.691 --> 31:00.459
Joanna Harris.

31:00.484 --> 31:02.279
Would you show them the tape, please?

31:02.955 --> 31:04.570
Couple of months ago,

31:04.595 --> 31:07.177
Joanna Harris was in the ED, pregnant.

31:07.202 --> 31:08.734
She lost the baby.

31:08.854 --> 31:11.339
22 weeks. Very sad case.

31:11.364 --> 31:13.067
So she impersonated
a healthcare worker

31:13.092 --> 31:15.032
to get to the PICU.

31:15.057 --> 31:17.510
It's entirely possible
that the trauma,

31:17.535 --> 31:19.331
coupled with the overwhelming fear

31:19.356 --> 31:20.790
of never being able to
carry a baby to term,

31:20.815 --> 31:22.539
uh, pushed her over the edge.

31:22.564 --> 31:24.581
But she seems to have thought
things out pretty thoroughly.

31:24.606 --> 31:26.874
I'd say her actions were
calculated, even predatory.

31:26.899 --> 31:29.300
Well, given what we know
about the patient,

31:29.325 --> 31:31.922
can you think of where
she might've gone?

31:31.947 --> 31:33.387
Some place she could hide.

31:33.412 --> 31:35.952
A supply closet or call room.

31:35.977 --> 31:37.999
Security teams
covered all those.

31:38.024 --> 31:39.215
According to the logs,

31:39.240 --> 31:42.400
Ms. Harris took our
maternity tour last May.

31:42.425 --> 31:43.667
Meaning?

31:43.692 --> 31:45.156
Well, isn't that
when we were transitioning

31:45.181 --> 31:46.943
between the old maternity
wing and the new one?

31:46.968 --> 31:48.086
Yes.

31:48.111 --> 31:50.045
She might know the old maternity wing.

31:50.070 --> 31:51.849
All right, let's go.

31:52.780 --> 31:59.404
<i>♪ </i>

31:59.890 --> 32:01.943
- Clear.
- Clear.

32:01.968 --> 32:04.937
[BABY CRYING]

32:05.187 --> 32:08.556
<i>♪ </i>

32:08.850 --> 32:12.372
[BABY CRYING, COUGHING]

32:12.427 --> 32:14.362
Hi, Joanna.

32:14.466 --> 32:16.400
I'm Dr. Charles.

32:16.561 --> 32:19.044
Stay away.
You're not taking him.

32:19.349 --> 32:22.311
Yeah, but the problem is
the baby is... is very sick.

32:22.458 --> 32:24.493
You can't have him.
He's mine.

32:24.518 --> 32:27.527
And I'm sure you want
the best for him, right?

32:27.552 --> 32:29.707
He needs medicine, antibiotics,

32:29.732 --> 32:31.392
or else he won't get better.

32:31.417 --> 32:32.917
The fact is,
if the baby doesn't get

32:32.942 --> 32:34.716
some treatment soon,

32:34.741 --> 32:36.358
uh, there's a chance he could die.

32:36.383 --> 32:37.419
No.

32:37.444 --> 32:39.909
None of us want that.
That's why we're here.

32:39.934 --> 32:41.514
We need to get him
back to his room,

32:41.539 --> 32:42.878
so he can get treated.

32:42.903 --> 32:45.052
<i>[DISQUIETING MUSIC]</i>

32:45.077 --> 32:46.704
Will you let us help him?

32:46.983 --> 32:50.019
<i>♪ </i>

32:50.248 --> 32:51.998
[SOBBING]

32:52.746 --> 32:54.492
I'm afraid.

32:54.517 --> 32:56.332
There's nothing to be afraid of.

32:56.357 --> 32:58.335
We understand why you did this.

32:58.360 --> 32:59.960
No one is gonna punish you.

33:00.473 --> 33:03.351
<i>♪ </i>

33:04.090 --> 33:05.826
What about them?

33:05.851 --> 33:09.292
They just wanna make sure
that the baby stays safe.

33:09.606 --> 33:11.865
Nothing bad is gonna
happen to you, I promise.

33:11.890 --> 33:13.639
Uh, well,
the important thing here

33:13.664 --> 33:15.554
is that we need to get some
treatment for the baby

33:15.579 --> 33:17.045
as soon as possible.

33:17.255 --> 33:20.191
<i>♪ </i>

33:20.381 --> 33:21.796
Give me the baby, Joanna.

33:21.821 --> 33:23.311
<i>♪ </i>

33:23.336 --> 33:24.872
I can't. I...

33:24.897 --> 33:27.133
Oh, you can.
You can, trust me.

33:27.158 --> 33:28.893
I'll protect you.

33:29.668 --> 33:36.740
<i>♪ </i>

33:47.701 --> 33:49.386
What? No.

33:49.411 --> 33:51.665
Why? I gave you the baby.

33:51.690 --> 33:53.024
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

33:53.049 --> 33:56.264
You... you lied to me. You lied to me.

33:56.289 --> 33:58.390
Why did she lie to me?

33:58.657 --> 34:05.697
<i>♪ </i>

34:10.866 --> 34:12.866
Yes.

34:12.900 --> 34:14.668
Thank you.

34:16.905 --> 34:18.839
Hey, everybody,

34:18.873 --> 34:20.808
they found the baby.

34:20.842 --> 34:23.911
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

34:27.518 --> 34:29.520
Let's make sure
you check in with Admitting.

34:29.554 --> 34:30.955
You will be seen in order of need.

34:30.989 --> 34:33.791
For those less seriously
ill or injured,

34:33.824 --> 34:35.326
try to be patient.

34:35.360 --> 34:36.694
We will get to you.

34:36.728 --> 34:38.661
Go ahead, sir. This way, yeah.

34:38.697 --> 34:40.598
[DEVICE BEEPS]

34:40.632 --> 34:43.601
<i>[SOFT, SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

34:43.635 --> 34:45.498
<i>♪ </i>

34:45.523 --> 34:47.847
Patient suffered
an ischemic stroke.

34:47.871 --> 34:50.440
Between the unsuccessful
attempt at intubation

34:50.475 --> 34:51.857
and the time it took to crich her,

34:51.882 --> 34:53.687
the patient's airway was
down for over a minute,

34:53.712 --> 34:55.478
starving the brain of oxygen.

34:55.513 --> 34:57.109
<i>♪ </i>

34:57.134 --> 34:58.825
Good thing you have
lawyers on retainer.

34:58.850 --> 35:00.645
Thank you, Dr. Abrams.

35:00.719 --> 35:03.354
<i>♪ </i>

35:03.521 --> 35:05.389
I didn't have any choice.

35:05.423 --> 35:08.029
All of our ED doctors were tied
up because of the lockdown,

35:08.054 --> 35:09.803
the patient was in laryngospasm.

35:09.828 --> 35:11.627
I couldn't get the
tubes past her chord.

35:11.652 --> 35:14.065
At that point, I had to crich her.

35:14.090 --> 35:16.383
Any doctor would have the same problem.

35:16.408 --> 35:18.673
Yeah, except, Maggie...

35:18.698 --> 35:20.332
they're doctors.

35:20.357 --> 35:22.910
They're allowed to perform
these procedures.

35:22.935 --> 35:24.502
Sharon, what would
you have done?

35:24.527 --> 35:25.993
Exactly what you did,

35:26.018 --> 35:28.804
but, unfortunately, that's
not going to help you.

35:28.829 --> 35:30.598
Sharon, am I gonna lose
my job over this?

35:30.623 --> 35:32.099
I hope not,

35:32.165 --> 35:35.181
but until I can figure something out...

35:35.503 --> 35:37.037
<i>♪ </i>

35:37.157 --> 35:39.458
I've got to suspend you, Maggie.

35:39.483 --> 35:41.785
- Sharon...
- I'm sorry.

35:42.016 --> 35:49.089
<i>♪ </i>

35:51.742 --> 35:53.643
The patient would've died.

35:53.668 --> 35:55.255
<i>♪ </i>

35:55.280 --> 35:57.281
I have no regrets.

35:57.798 --> 36:04.804
<i>♪ </i>

36:17.117 --> 36:19.084
I know what you're gonna say.

36:19.109 --> 36:21.382
I should not have lied to Joanna.

36:21.407 --> 36:22.708
It was wrong.

36:22.733 --> 36:24.425
She's just a desperate, troubled woman,

36:24.450 --> 36:25.985
not a psychopath.

36:26.667 --> 36:28.501
I agree.

36:28.652 --> 36:30.987
She's not, but am I?
Am I a psychopath?

36:31.012 --> 36:32.248
What?

36:32.273 --> 36:34.027
Look how easily I lied to her,

36:34.052 --> 36:36.034
how I coldly manipulated her.

36:36.157 --> 36:37.429
In this context,

36:37.454 --> 36:38.864
that's hardly an
indication of psychopathy.

36:38.889 --> 36:39.942
Well, how about my life?

36:39.967 --> 36:42.324
Would you say that I'm able to
form lasting relationships?

36:42.349 --> 36:43.739
I mean, I have no real friends,

36:43.764 --> 36:45.890
no significant romantic attachments.

36:45.915 --> 36:48.891
I think I have emotions, but
maybe they aren't real.

36:48.916 --> 36:50.647
Maybe they're just imitative.

36:50.672 --> 36:52.171
You just told me
that you felt guilty

36:52.196 --> 36:53.757
about lying to a patient,

36:53.782 --> 36:56.116
which means that you have a conscience,

36:56.141 --> 36:58.479
which means that you're
not a psychopath.

36:58.504 --> 37:01.141
Whatever you wanna call it,
I am my father's daughter.

37:01.215 --> 37:04.120
Well... well,
you're also my resident,

37:04.347 --> 37:06.515
and I find you to be a...

37:06.667 --> 37:09.002
A deeply compassionate person,

37:09.301 --> 37:11.880
who's capable of great empathy.

37:12.328 --> 37:14.021
I just never would've roped you into

37:14.046 --> 37:16.888
this whole psychiatry thing

37:16.913 --> 37:19.982
if I wasn't entirely convinced of that.

37:26.212 --> 37:27.846
See you tomorrow?

37:28.723 --> 37:35.796
<i>♪ </i>

37:38.094 --> 37:40.195
[EXHALES] Thanks, man.

37:40.220 --> 37:41.554
He should wake up pretty soon.

37:41.579 --> 37:42.714
- Yeah.
- Nice work today.

37:42.739 --> 37:44.275
- You too.
- Yeah.

37:44.624 --> 37:46.592
<i>♪ </i>

37:46.617 --> 37:48.047
Dr. Bekker...

37:48.072 --> 37:50.129
have you come to see me or our patient?

37:50.154 --> 37:52.022
<i>♪ </i>

37:52.047 --> 37:53.716
How's he doing?

37:53.982 --> 37:55.736
I think he's gonna make it.

37:55.855 --> 37:58.204
- It's a long day, huh?
- [SIGHS, CHUCKLES] Yeah.

37:58.229 --> 37:59.897
<i>♪ </i>

38:00.039 --> 38:01.907
I could go for a meal.

38:01.932 --> 38:04.427
<i>♪ </i>

38:04.452 --> 38:06.920
I'd, uh, check the cafeteria.

38:06.945 --> 38:08.357
It's Tuesday.

38:08.382 --> 38:10.068
It's meatloaf.

38:10.718 --> 38:12.249
My favorite.

38:12.274 --> 38:13.852
[CHUCKLES]

38:13.877 --> 38:15.711
<i>♪ </i>

38:15.785 --> 38:17.452
Good night.

38:17.972 --> 38:25.045
<i>♪ </i>

38:33.153 --> 38:35.054
Dr. Halstead.

38:35.079 --> 38:36.880
I owe you an apology.

38:37.143 --> 38:38.810
Gary Taylor's autopsy revealed

38:38.835 --> 38:40.560
that he died from cardiac failure,

38:40.585 --> 38:43.547
not an adverse drug reaction
or metastatic cancer.

38:43.572 --> 38:46.174
In fact, in the hours from the
time he was given the drugs

38:46.199 --> 38:47.967
until he died,

38:47.992 --> 38:50.961
the mass actually
shrank one centimeter.

38:51.062 --> 38:53.897
That off-label cocktail
of yours, it worked.

38:53.922 --> 38:56.072
I let Ms. Goodwin know.
Congratulations.

38:56.097 --> 38:58.973
Uh... um, look, uh,
it wasn't my idea.

38:58.998 --> 39:00.632
<i>♪ </i>

39:00.657 --> 39:02.387
It was Dr. Manning's.

39:02.412 --> 39:04.141
Okay, whatever.

39:04.166 --> 39:05.824
We've been thinking about launching

39:05.849 --> 39:08.250
- a Phase One clinical trial to...
- Excuse me.

39:08.466 --> 39:12.241
<i>♪ </i>

39:12.467 --> 39:14.234
- Whoa, Nat, hold up...
- [CAR CHIRPS]

39:14.259 --> 39:16.142
You're gonna get the
credit you deserve.

39:16.167 --> 39:17.133
I'll make sure of that.

39:17.158 --> 39:19.205
You think that's
what's bothering me?

39:19.230 --> 39:21.408
Look, I know I shouldn't
have taken the blame,

39:21.433 --> 39:22.833
and I certainly don't
deserve the credit.

39:22.858 --> 39:24.525
Will, stop.

39:24.550 --> 39:26.220
Just stop.

39:26.245 --> 39:28.805
My whole career, from med school on,

39:28.830 --> 39:30.657
I keep running into the same problem:

39:30.682 --> 39:33.339
men who either dismiss
me or patronize me,

39:33.364 --> 39:35.517
who cannot see me as an equal.

39:35.542 --> 39:37.898
- Well, I see you as an equal.
- No, you don't.

39:37.929 --> 39:40.462
And it's not just today.
It keeps happening.

39:40.487 --> 39:43.266
- Natalie...
- Look, I know you love me,

39:43.291 --> 39:45.428
but in a way, that's
part of the problem.

39:45.453 --> 39:47.997
You can only see me as
the woman you love,

39:48.022 --> 39:50.661
the woman you need to
protect and take care of,

39:50.686 --> 39:53.236
and in a way, that limits me.

39:53.261 --> 39:55.736
It puts me in a kind of jail.

39:55.858 --> 39:58.690
Look, I don't want that,
Natalie.

39:58.715 --> 40:00.507
Let's talk about this.

40:00.532 --> 40:02.253
We'll figure it out.

40:02.654 --> 40:04.655
Maybe we can,

40:04.680 --> 40:07.036
but right now, I need a break, okay?

40:07.061 --> 40:08.629
I love you...

40:08.654 --> 40:10.695
but I need a break from us.

40:10.720 --> 40:12.522
No, come on.

40:12.547 --> 40:15.515
<i>[SOLEMN MUSIC]</i>

40:15.945 --> 40:17.245
<i>♪ </i>

40:17.318 --> 40:19.887
